Boil the potatoes: Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees. Cut the @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch cubes. Place them in a #pot{} with a large pinch of @salt{pinch} and enough water to cover by 1 inch. Bring to a boil and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}, until fork-tender.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @Panko Breadcrumbs{¼%cup}, @Parmesan Cheese{¼%cup}, a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%teaspoon}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @Pepper{pinch}. Place the @Chicken Breasts{12%ounce} on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{} and season with salt and pepper on all sides. Spread each chicken breast with @Dijon Mustard{2%teaspoon}. Divide the panko mixture between each chicken breast and press onto the chicken to adhere. Place in the oven for ~{15-20%minutes}, until cooked through and the juices run clear when pierced with a knife.

While the chicken cooks, halve the @Grape Tomatoes{4%ounce}. Thinly slice the @Scallions{2%unit}, keeping the greens and whites separate. Mince or grate the @Garlic{2%clove}.

With about 8 minutes left to go on the chicken, remove the baking sheet from the oven and toss the tomatoes on one side with the scallion whites, garlic, and a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%teaspoon}. Season with @Salt{pinch} and @Pepper{pinch}. Return the baking sheet to the oven for ~{7-8%minutes}, until the tomatoes burst and the chicken finishes cooking.

Once the potatoes are done, drain and place in a #large bowl{}. Toss with the scallion greens, @Balsamic Vinegar{1%tablespoon}, and a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{3%teaspoon}. Season with salt and pepper.